headline: 3 Reasons KEY is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: KeyCorp’s 18.2% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 12.3%, and its stock price has climbed to $21.50 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
